abstract.value: The Donald Oliver/Chelsea Music Archive consists of documents collected both personally by Donald Oliver and by Chelsea Music Services. Chelsea Music Services, Inc. was established as a “music factory of six or seven orchestrators willing to step in when needed.” It became one of Broadway’s favored music preparation services, producing “green-books,” handwritten, and bound piano-conductor scores until 1988. The collection consists of librettos, piano-vocal scores, orchestrations, and video recordings pertaining to Broadway and Off-Broadway musicals. Among the prominent productions featured in the collection are <emph render="italic">A Chorus Line</emph>, <emph render="italic">The Phantom of the Opera</emph>, <emph render="italic">Breakfast at Tiffany’s</emph>, and  <emph render="italic">Merrily We Roll Along</emph>. The collection also documents the work of individual theater personalities, including actor Mandy Patinkin, performer Marti Stevens, and lyricist Dorothy Fields. Additional material includes playbills, newspaper clippings of reviews, screenplays and teleplays.

p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.

following form: Identification of item,  date (if known); Donald Oliver/Chelsea Music Archive; MSS 254; box number; folder number; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University Libraries.
The collection was donated to NYU's Fales Library by Don Oliver in 2009. An accretion was later received in September 2016; the accession number associated with this gift is 2016.047.

Series I: Librettos and PlaybillsScope and Content

This series is comprised of original and photocopied librettos for Broadway and Off-Broadway productions. The bulk of this series consists of the librettos, which are in various stages of production, ranging from final versions, rehearsal, and draft copies. Many of the librettos include annotations and edits, which are noted in the finding aid. Also included in this series are playbills and newspaper clippings of theater reviews.

Series III: Conductor Scores and OrchestrationsScope and Content

This series consists of piano conductor scores, master scores and parts, and full orchestrations for Broadway and off-Broadway productions. The bulk of the collection consists of bound and handwritten “green-books” and spiral-bound piano conductor scores. This series also comprises production scores for several theater personalities, including cabaret singer Marti Stevens (b.1933) and librettist and lyricist Dorothy Fields (1905-1974). Also included in this series are full orchestrations for Mandy Patinkin’s stage productions of his albums Kidults and Mama-Loshn.
